"Ethnobiology is an interdisciplinary field examining dynamic relationships between human societies, biological organisms (primarily plants and animals), and their environments. It integrates perspectives from anthropology, botany, zoology, ecology, linguistics, and increasingly, sustainability science, ethics, and decolonial studies. 

